<document>
	<title>Implications of cystic fibrosis for health services and the
   afflicted.</title>

	<author>Frydman-M-I.</author>

	<source>Soc-Sci-Med. 1979 Mar. 13A(2). P 147-50. (REVIEW).</source>

	<abstract>&quot;Psychosocial&quot; literature on cystic fibrosis (CF) is critically
   reviewed.  Major methodological shortcomings include the anecdotal
   nature of findings, overemphasis on negative consequences of the
   disease, and the lack of a suitable theoretical framework.  Avenues
   for future research are suggested.</abstract>

